metatags.og:title: Bart Simpson
metatags.og:description: Bartholomew JoJo "Bart" Simpson (born April 1, 1979) is one of the main characters of The Simpsons. Bart is the mischievous, rebellious, misunderstood, disruptive and "potentially dangerous" eldest child. He is the only son of Homer and Marge Simpson, and the older brother of Lisa and Maggie. He also has been nicknamed "Cosmo", after discovering a comet in "Bart's Comet". Bart has also been on the cover on numerous comics, such as "Critical Hit", "Simpsons Treasure Trove#11", and "Winter...

His great-nephew Bart Simpson's middle name was presumably named after him (hence Bartholomew JoJo Simpson). metatags.og:description: Jessica Lovejoy is the rebellious daughter of Reverend Lovejoy and Helen Lovejoy. She is Bart's biggest crush after Laura Powers and first girlfriend as well. Nelson Muntz thinks she's innocent. She was featured as both Bart Simpson's love interest and the main antagonist of Bart's Girlfriend. There have been 150 commercials for Butterfinger that aired on Fox, FX and Fox News Channel, which featured The Simpsons beginning in 1988, when America's Most Wanted first aired on Fox before moving to Lifetime in 2011. Many of the commercials featured Homer trying to get Bart's Butterfinger, but would be one-upped by Bart each time. metatags.og:description: El Barto is Bart Simpson's graffiti-tagging alter-ego and is one of the most infamous outlaws in Springfield. El Barto's writings known as graffiti are around Springfield. This long-running joke has never been unveiled by anyone -law enforcer or otherwise- to anyone in Springfield, even with a large number of clues given throughout the series. metatags.og:title: Jenda Simpson
metatags.og:description: Jenda (formerly Jenda Simpson) is Bart's future girlfriend and eventual ex-wife. Eight years into the future Jenda is dating Bart Simpson. They attend prom together, and on the same night on a picnic, he proposes to her, but Jenda turns him down and breaks up with him due to him not having any plans for the future where he can provide for them.
